%N A392100 Array listed by rows: Pythagorean triples a < b < c such that a + b and a + b + 2*c are prime, sorted first by increasing perimeter and then by the even term.
%C A392100 All triples are primitive.
%C A392100 The perimeter of a Pythagorean triple is never prime; the primes a + b and a + b + 2*c are (perimeter - hypotenuse) and (perimeter + hypotenuse).
%H A392100 Robert Israel, <a href="/A392100/b392100.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10500</a> (rows 1 to 3500, flattened)
%e A392100 Row 3 is (28, 45, 53): this is Pythagorean since 28^2 + 45^2 = 2809 = 53^2, and 28 + 45 = 73 and 28 + 45 + 2*53 = 179 are prime.
%e A392100 Array starts:
%e A392100     3     4     5
%e A392100     5    12    13
%e A392100    28    45    53
%e A392100    11    60    61
%e A392100    36    77    85
%e A392100    65    72    97
%e A392100    15   112   113
%e A392100    24   143   145
%p A392100 N:= 2000: # for triples with perimeter <= N
%p A392100 R:= NULL:
%p A392100 for x from 1 while 2*x^2 < N do
%p A392100   for y from 1 to x-1 while 2*x^2 + 2*x*y <= N do
%p A392100     if igcd(x,y)=1 and isprime(x^2+2*x*y - y^2) and isprime(3*x^2 + 2*x*y + y^2) then R:= R, [x^2-y^2,2*x*y,x^2+y^2]
%p A392100 fi od od:
%p A392100 sorter:= proc(a,b) local pa,pb;
%p A392100    pa:= a[1]+a[2]+a[3]; pb:= b[1]+b[2]+b[3];
%p A392100    if pa = pb then a[2] < b[2] else pa < pb fi
%p A392100 end proc:
%p A392100 map(sort,sort([R],sorter));
